ELIABETH OLLEMAR, PROSECUTOR, v. TOWN OF IRVINGTON, IN THE COUNTY OF ESSEX, RESPONDENT. Argued May 6, 1930 Decided May 7, 1930.

Before Justices Parker, Campbell and Bodine.

Eor the plaintiff, Reed & Reynolds. Eor the defendant, Charles E. Stewart. Per Curiam.

Our examination of the facts and argument presented lead us to the conclusion that the application for the writ of certiorari should be denied.
